org.cloudgraph.recognizer

Class GraphRecognizerDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudgraph.recognizer.GraphRecognizerDetector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExprVisitor

    public class GraphRecognizerDetector
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExprVisitor
    A simple query expression visitor which determines whether a graph recognizer is required, within the context of a binary (query) expression syntax tree, encapsulating operator precedence and other factors.

    Visits the expression tree and for each expression determines whether the property and its path are represented within the row key model for the current graph by a user defined field. If not, then the property and its expression are outside the row key and can't be represented by a scan. Therefore a recognizer is required.

    Since:
    0.5.8
    Author:
    Scott Cinnamond
